27/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- During a visit to Pristina Friday (25 March), Slovenian Foreign Minister and current OSCE Chairman-in-Office Dimitrij Rupel again called for multiethnic dialogue in Kosovo, stressing that no lasting solution to the Kosovo problem could be found without co-operation with local Serbs as well as authorities in Belgrade.
UNMIK chief Soren Jessen Petersen, who is due to visit Belgrade next week, also urged the Serbian government to engage in serious dialogue with Pristina.
(AFP, OSCE Web site, Tanjug - 25/03/05)
